I"Ò<p>Exosomatic <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/memory-is-perception-of-structural-artifacts">memories</a> often resemble cues for endosomatic memory, rather than integral memories in themselves. <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/virtual-agents-encourage-social-snacking">Photos of a loved one</a> trigger <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/second-brain-contents-resemble-long-term-memory">positive memories</a>. Even in the more semantic memories stored in a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/second-brain-has-a-cognitive-architecture">second brain</a>, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/written-word-is-a-proxy-for-thought">entries are just proxies for thoughts</a>.</p>
